By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) –  Plateau state on Tuesday led the COVID-19 infection table with 50 patients as new confirmed cases dropped to 252, the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control has said. The health agency which released the report via it’s twitter handle said these new confirmed cases bring total confirmed cases to 52,800 out of which 39,964 have been treated and discharged from across different isolation centres in Nigeria. Regrettably, the NCDC added that 1,007 lives have been lost in the country for COVID-19 related complications since the index case was recorded in February 2020. The NCDC’s report released further revealed that the 252 cases recorded from 18 States including FCT are as follows: Plateau-50Enugu-35Rivers-27Lagos-26FCT-18Kaduna-18Ekiti-10Kano-10Taraba-9Anambra-8Edo-8Oyo-8Delta-7Ogun-6Abia-5Bayelsa-5Ebonyi-1Osun-1 The state by state breakdown of reported cases in Nigeria is contained in the table below: By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - The Health agency in charge of COVID-19 in Nigeria said that 290 new cases of COVID-19 have been recorded, bringing the total confirmed cases to  46,867 in the country. The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control also said that it has also recorded five… August 11, 2020 In "Top Stories" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - Three states - Lagos, FCT and Plateau accounted for 53.9 percent of the 453 new cases of COVID-19 infections recorded in Nigeria on Wednesday, the report of the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control has revealed. These three states recorded 113, 72 and 59… August 13, 2020 In "Top Stories" By Chibuike Nwabuk Abuja (Sundiata Post) - The reported cases of COVID-19 infections Thursday shrunk to 373 compared to the 473 cases recorded on Wednesday, the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control report has shown. However, there was a reported increase in death toll from 956 the previous day (Wednesday) to… August 14, 2020 In "Top Stories"